# Novo Prototype roadmap

## Completed

- **Patient portal home (`patient-home.html`) (Mar 2026):** New page after **Create account** (Figma `373:3867`): dark nav (`#012d20`), hero band (`#045037`) + `assets/portal-hero-decoration.svg`, welcome copy, **Next steps** card (accent step `palette.accent` 50/700), questionnaire CTA, **How we can support you** video card (`portal-video-thumb.png`, `portal-play-circle.svg`), **Quick links** (warn-100 + info-100 icon wells per token), footer with `semantic.elevation1` border. **Inter** + Material Symbols; **CSS variables** map to `design-tokens.json` (`color.palette`, `semantic`, `typography.roles.desktop`). `completion.step1.cta.href` → `patient-home.html`; `questionnaire.js` appends `?first=` / `&name=` from `answers.contact.name`. `flowId` → `eligibility-v5`.
- **Thank-you screen (Mar 2026):** Replaced the old single-block completion with the Figma **Thank you!** flow (`1180:4266`): success icon + headline/lead, **Next steps** (numbered 1–2, full-width **Create account** CTA, trial overview copy), second card **Need help?** (FAQs + Contact with mailto), optional **Change your responses** link below. Completion content lives in `questionnaire.json` under `completion` (`headline`, `lead`, `step1`, `step2`, `help`); legacy `title`/`body` still map to `headline`/`lead` via `questionnaire.js`. Submit hides `#intake-card` and shows `#intake-complete` (no progress bar). `flowId` → `eligibility-v4`.
- **Review step before completion (Mar 2026):** After the last question, the flow shows a **Summary / Review and confirm your answers** screen (Figma Patient portal `1180:4147`): numbered rows per step with answer + edit (pencil), **Back** returns to the last question, **Submit questionnaire** leads to the existing thank-you `completion` screen. Copy and CTA label come from optional `review` in `questionnaire.json`. `flowId` bumped to `eligibility-v3` so prior session state resets cleanly.
- **Intake sidebar title (Mar 2026):** `#intake-sidebar-title` (`.intake-sidebar__title`) uses `--fs-headline-6` (20px); `--fs-headline-5`/`--fs-headline-6` added in `:root` to match `design-tokens.json` desktop headline scale.
- **Age field width (Mar 2026):** The `age` text step uses optional JSON `inputWidth: "chunk"` plus `maxLength: 3` and `inputMode: "numeric"`. CSS class `.intake-input--chunk` caps width with `ch` + horizontal padding so the control matches ~3 digits instead of full-row `width: 100%`.
- **Questionnaire opening steps (Mar 2026):** First step is patient vs caregiver (`respondent-role`); second is free-text age (`age`). Replaced the prior 18+ yes/no gate and the old diagnosis-as-second-step ordering.
- **Questionnaire select (Mar 2026):** Step 3 (`diagnosis`) uses JSON `type: "select"` (native `<select>`) with a fixed list of rare blood diseases; `questionnaire.js` validates `select` like `radio`. Selects use `width: max-content` with `max-width: 100%`. The chevron is a custom SVG background (`appearance: none`) so spacing from the border is not controlled by the OS native arrow (which ignores padding).
- **Contact step (Mar 2026):** After contact preference, `type: "contact"` renders name + email + phone on one screen; answers stored under `answers.contact` as `{ name, email, phone }`. `flowId` bumped to `eligibility-v2` so old session state clears.
- **Wordmark / Novo mark 0×0 fix (Mar 2026):** External SVGs with root `width`/`height` of `100%` collapse as `<img>`; both `logo-mytomorrows.svg` and `logo.svg` now use viewBox + explicit pixel dimensions on the root where needed. `.site-logo img` uses fixed `height`, `aspect-ratio: 310 / 39`, and `object-fit: contain` so layout never depends on flaky intrinsic sizing when paired with `max-height`/`height: auto`.
- **Logo placement & Figma wordmark (Mar 2026):** On `questionnaire.html`, the myTomorrows wordmark from Figma node `48:2036` (`assets/logo-mytomorrows.svg`) sits in the **top nav bar** (header); the navy **Novo** mark (`assets/logo.svg`, 104×74) sits in the **sidebar** above “Medical intake”. Landing page (`index.html`) header uses the **Novo** mark (`assets/logo.svg`); `body#top .site-logo img` overrides `aspect-ratio` to `104 / 74` so it does not inherit the wordmark ratio. `sidebarLogo` was removed from `questionnaire.json` and related JS.
- **Intake AI disclaimer removed (Mar 2026):** Dropped the footer disclaimer paragraph, `disclaimer` field in `questionnaire.json`, and related JS/CSS; card body padding no longer reserves space for that strip.
- **Eligibility questionnaire (Mar 2026):** Data-driven flow on `questionnaire.html` with content in `questionnaire.json` (add/remove steps and types without HTML changes) and renderer in `questionnaire.js`. Styling uses CSS variables aligned with `design-tokens.json` (primary `#007c50`, text `#012d20`, neutrals, spacing scale). Session persistence via `sessionStorage`. Landing CTAs “See if you qualify” and “Eligibility check” link to `questionnaire.html`. Serve the folder over HTTP so `fetch('questionnaire.json')` works (not `file://`).
- **Hover affordances (Mar 2026):** Stronger color-only hovers (no shadows or lift): nav links and inactive role tabs shift to `--color-line` (`#005cda`); primary buttons use a lighter navy (`--color-navy-hover`); trial list rows use a more visible sky-tinted row background (`--color-trial-row-hover`).
- **Landing page (Mar 2025):** Static stack (`index.html`, `styles.css`, `app.js`) implementing Figma frames `41:1286` (patients) and `41:1350` (physicians). Audience switcher via tabs; typography/colors from design (Noto Sans, `#001a69`, `#dff1fb`). Image assets copied into `assets/` from Figma MCP URLs (time-limited remote URLs replaced for durability). `design-tokens.json` is the reference for the medical intake page (`:root` token variables in `styles.css`); the LP itself still uses its original navy/sky palette.
- **Step badges (Mar 2026):** “How it works” step markers are HTML (`span.step__badge` with 1–3) + CSS circles instead of PNGs (`step-1.png` … `step-3-phys.png`), keeping 42×42px and `aria-hidden` on the decorative number (list semantics stay on the `<ol>`).
- **Physician trial card icons (Mar 2026):** Google Material Symbols Outlined, one glyph per row by content (`water_drop`, `bloodtype`, `science`, `view_list`; NDec row uses `science` instead of `microscope` to avoid `mic`/microphone ligature clash) via fonts.googleapis.com instead of PNGs in the trial list.
- **Hero CTAs (Mar 2026):** Buttons in `.hero__copy` use `align-self: flex-start` so they size to their label and sit left-aligned with the copy column (flex column default was stretching them full width).
- **Hero titles (Mar 2026):** `.hero__title` uses `line-height: 1.2` instead of matching `font-size` 1:1 so wrapped headlines have comfortable vertical rhythm (desktop + tablet breakpoints).
- **Hero padding parity (Mar 2026):** Removed `.hero__inner--physician { align-items: center; }` so the physician hero uses the same top alignment as the patient hero (`flex-start` on `.hero__inner`); vertical centering had made the sky band look like extra padding.
- **Trial card links (Mar 2026):** Physician trial list rows use real `href`s (prototype search URL + mytomorrows.com). `app.js` only `preventDefault`s `.trial-card__row` clicks when `href` is missing or `#` so placeholder rows stay inert but linked rows navigate.

## Decisions

- **Questionnaire completion (Mar 2026):** The thank-you screen remains the final state after **Submit questionnaire** on the review step. The review screen is not a JSON `step` type; it is rendered when the user finishes the last configured step (`questionnaire.js` `showReview` / `reviewing` in `sessionStorage`).
- **Trial card links (Mar 2026):** `.trial-card__row` listeners only call `preventDefault()` when `href` is missing or `#` (placeholder rows). Real `http(s):` URLs navigate normally; the previous blanket `preventDefault()` blocked all trial list links.
- **Questionnaire content:** Editable in `questionnaire.json` only (steps, copy, `showSkip`, field `type`). No separate CMS for the prototype.
- **Closing screen (Mar 2026):** Completion copy lives under `completion` with structured fields (`headline`, `lead`, `nextStepsHeading`, `step1` + `cta`, `step2.paragraphs`, `help` with `faqCard` / `contactCard`). Legacy `title` maps to `headline`; `returnLink` was removed in favor of **Create account**, FAQ, and email links in the thank-you layout.
- **Edit from completion (Mar 2026):** Optional `completion.changeResponses` (`label`); set to `false` to hide. Shown as underlined text control `.intake-done-change` below the thank-you cards (not the old back + primary footer).
- **Git / GitHub (Mar 2026):** Repository is scoped to this folder only (`git init` here), not the parent `Documents` tree. Remote: `https://github.com/kbogers/novo-prototype` (`main`). Added `.gitignore` for `.DS_Store`.
- Nav links scroll within the **active** panel only (`data-scroll-section` + `data-scroll-target`). Patient panel ends after “How it works” (no trials/FAQs placeholders). Physician panel ends after “How it works” (FAQ placeholder removed Mar 2026).
- **Features (“How it works”):** Header and steps list use `max-width: 800px`, `width: 100%`, and `margin: 0 auto` so they’re centered in `features__inner`; copy stays left-aligned (`text-align: left` on the header).
